        </div>
    </div>
</div>
<br>
<p class="offset-1 col-10">Players may also notice stacks of cards on the Research Line.  If there is more than one
    card in a stack, the speller may use up to that many of that Letter in their word.  If there are bets on that
    Letter, they must pay for EACH use of the letter.
</p>


 
<br>
<br>
<h3 class="offset-1 col-10">End of the Round:</h3>
<p class="offset-1 col-10">The spelling player makes money in two ways -- the length of the word, and the Ledgers 
    on the Letters they used.  The amount of money gained from the length of the word is shown on the top row.
    For example, a speller would gain 4&#162; from the bank for a 4-letter word.  The amount of money gained from 
    Ledgers is the money in the center of the Reasearch Line Letters they used in the spelled word.
</p>
<p class="offset-1 col-10">You can see these changes reflected in the score.  You can view everyone's score at any 
    time by clicking on 'scores' at the top of the screen.
</p>
<div class="col-10 offset-1">
    <div class="row">
